quran[14]{c,v,t,f}:
43,34,"and (silver) doors to their houses, and couches (of silver) upon which they would recline; {1}",footnotes:1:That is
43,35,"or that they be made of gold. Surely all this is only the enjoyment of the life of the world. But (true prosperity) in the Hereafter with Your Lord is only for the God-fearing."
43,36,"He who is negligent to remember the Merciful One, {1} to him We assign a satan as his boon companion,",footnotes:1:Dhikrir Rahman: His remembrance as well as His
admonition and the Quran.
43,37,"and these satans hinder them from the Right Path, while he still reckons himself to be rightly-guided."
43,38,"But when he comes to Us, he will say (to his satan): “Would that there had been between me and you the distance as between the East and the West. How evil a companion you were!”"
43,39,"(He will then be told): “Today it will not benefit you the least that after your wrong-doing you and your satans now share the chastisement.” {1}",footnotes:1:That is
43,40,"Can you, (O Prophet), then make the deaf hear, or direct to the Right Way the blind or one lost in manifest error? {1}",footnotes:1:It means to say: Pay attention to those who are inclined to listen and have not closed their eyes to the realities
43,41,"We shall inflict retribution on them, whether We take you away from the world (before We do that),"
43,42,"or make you see the end that We had promised them, for We have full power over them. {1}",footnotes:1:This thing can be understood fully only by keeping in view the background in which it was said. The disbelievers of Makkah thought that the person of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) had become a source of trouble for them. If they could somehow get rid of him
43,43,"So hold fast to what has been revealed to you. Surely you are on the Straight Way. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
43,44,"Verily it is a great source of eminence for you and your people, and soon you will be called to account concerning that. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
43,45,"Ask all Our Messengers whom We sent before you whether We had appointed any deities beside the Merciful One to be worshipped. {1}",footnotes:1:Ask the Messengers: Find out from the Books brought by them. Just as the meaning of: “If there arises any dispute among you about anything
43,46,"Indeed We {1} sent Moses with Our Signs {2} to Pharaoh and his nobles. He told them: “I am a Messenger of the Lord of the Universe.”",footnotes:1:This story has been narrated here for three objects:(1) That when Allah sends His Prophet to a country and nation and affords it the opportunity which He has now given to the Arabs by appointing the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) to Prophethood
43,47,"Yet when he brought forth Clear Signs from Us, then lo, they burst into laughter."
